VI'm going to tell you what we have learned.
p108
aVThe implicit association test, which measures unconscious bias,
p109
aVyou can go online and take it.
p110
aVFive million people have taken it.
p111
aVTurns out, our default is white. We like white people.
p112
aVWe prefer white. What do I mean by that?
p113
aVWhen people are shown images  of black men and white men,
p114
aVwe are more quickly able to associate
p115
aVthat picture with a positive word, that white person with a positive word,
p116
aVthan we are when we are  trying to associate
p117
aVpositive with a black face, and vice versa.
p118
aVWhen we see a black face,
p119
aVit is easier for us to connect black with negative
p120
aVthan it is white with negative.
p121
aVSeventy percent of white people taking that test prefer white.
p122
aVFifty percent of black people taking that test prefer white.
p123
aVYou see, we were all outside when the contamination came down.
