p126
aVYou know, one of the things that you probably are thinking about,
p127
aVand you're probably like, you know what,
p128
aVI'm just going to double down on my color blindness.
p129
aVYes, I'm going to recommit to that.
p130
aVI'm going to suggest to you, no.
p131
aVWe've gone about as far as we can go trying to make a difference
p132
aVtrying to not see color.
p133
aVThe problem was never that we saw color. It was what we did when we saw the color.
p134
aVIt's a false ideal.
p135
aVAnd while we're busy  pretending not to see,
p136
aVwe are not being aware of the ways in which racial difference
p137
aVis changing people's possibilities, that's keeping them from thriving,
